            <h3>What is System Monitor?</h3>
            <p>
                System Monitor is a lightweight, web-based application that provides
                real-time insights into your computer's performance. Built with
                <strong>Node.js</strong>, <strong>Express.js</strong> and <strong>EJS</strong>, it displays key system
                metrics such as CPU usage, RAM consumption, disk utilization, uptime,
                and network information — all in a clean, minimalistic dashboard.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="about-section">
        <div class="about-icon">
            <i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="about-content">
            <h3>Why was it built?</h3>
            <p>
                The main goal of this project was to learn Node.js, Express.js and 
                familiarize myself with them, while also providing a simple alternative 
                to built-in task managers.
                Instead of opening a desktop application, you can monitor your machine
                from any browser — on any device connected to your local network.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>
